[section#time.clock.req
    [:en] [^:oc Clock] requirements
    [:zh_CN] [^:oc Clock] 的规定
]

[para]
[:en]
A clock is a bundle consisting of a [`duration], a [`time_point], and a function
[`now()] to get the current [`time_point].
[:zh_CN]
时钟是由一种 [`duration]，一种 [`time_point]，以及一个用以获得当前 [`time_point]
的函数 [`now()] 所构成的组合。

[:en]
The origin of the clock[=']s [`time_point] is referred to as the clock[=']s
[+epoch].
[:zh_CN]
时钟的 [`time_point] 的原点被称为该时钟的[+纪元]。

[:en]
A clock shall meet the requirements in [#:tab#time.clock].
[:zh_CN]
时钟应当满足 [#:tab#time.clock] 中的规定。

[para]
[:en]
In [#:tab#time.clock] [`C1] and [`C2] denote clock types.
[:zh_CN]
[#:tab#time.clock] 中，[`C1] 和 [`C2] 均代表时钟类型。

[:en]
[`t1] and [`t2] are values returned by [`C1::now()] where the call returning
[`t1] happens before ([#intro.multithread]) the call returning [`t2] and both of
these calls occur before [`C1::time_point::max()].
[:zh_CN]
[`t1] 和 [`t2] 是由 [`C1::now()] 所返回的值，其中返回 [`t1] 的调用发生早于
（[#intro.multithread]）返回 [`t2] 的调用，且这些调用均发生早于
[`C1::time_point::max()]。

[begin:note]
[:en]
This means [`C1] did not wrap around between [`t1] and [`t2].
[:zh_CN]
其含义为 [`C1] 不会在 [`t1] 和 [`t2] 之间回绕。
[end:note]

