[para]
[begin:note]
[:en]
The relative difference in durations between those reported by a given clock and
the SI definition is a measure of the quality of implementation.
[:zh_CN]
给定时钟所报出的时间间隔，和 SI 定义之间的相对误差，是实现的质量的度量。
[end:note]

[para]
[:en]
A type [`TC] meets the [^:oc TrivialClock] requirements if:
[:zh_CN]
类型 [`TC] 满足 [^:oc TrivialClock] 的规定，如果：

[list]
[item]
[:en] [`TC] meets the [^:oc Clock] requirements ([#time.clock.req]),
[:zh_CN] [`TC] 满足 [^:oc Clock] 的规定（[#time.clock.req]），

[item]
[:en] the types [`TC::rep], [`TC::duration], and [`TC::time_point] meet the
[^:oc EqualityComparable] ([#:tab#cpp17.equalitycomparable]) and
[^:oc LessThanComparable] ([#:tab#cpp17.lessthancomparable]) requirements and
the requirements of numeric types ([#numeric.requirements]).
[:zh_CN] 类型 [`TC::rep]、[`TC::duration] 和 [`TC::time_point] 满足
[^:oc EqualityComparable]（[#:tab#cpp17.equalitycomparable]）和
[^:oc LessThanComparable]（[#:tab#cpp17.lessthancomparable]）的规定，以及对数值
类型的规定（[#numeric.requirements]）。

[begin:note]
[:en]
This means, in particular, that operations on these types will not throw
exceptions.
[:zh_CN]
尤其是，对这些类型的操作不能抛出异常。
[end:note]

[item]
[:en] lvalues of the types [`TC::rep], [`TC::duration], and [`TC::time_point]
are swappable ([#swappable.requirements]),
[:zh_CN] 类型 [`TC::rep]、[`TC::duration] 和 [`TC::time_point] 的左值是可交换的
（[#swappable.requirements]），

[item]
[:en] the function [`TC::now()] does not throw exceptions, and
[:zh_CN] 函数 [`TC::now()] 不抛出异常，并且

[item]
[:en] the type [`TC::time_point::clock] meets the [^:oc TrivialClock]
requirements, recursively.
[:zh_CN] 类型 [`TC::time_point::clock] 递归地符合 [^:oc TrivialClock] 的规定。
[list:end]
